<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Kivko</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-04-17 19:47:07</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Yea, me again. Anyway, it's true that you can kill rogue clockworks in Steamfont and just use the blackboxes on those (correct me if im wrong), but the problem is, the faction and the fact that rogue clockworks aren't exactly all over the place and don't come out that often. I usually hunt for them near the windmills and after about a day's worth of killing I only saw 5 and 1 out of 5 of those clockworks had a rusted blackbox. <BR>
<BR>
It would take you a LONG time to collect many of those blackboxes from killing rogue clockworks. The good part about RedV and his little bast*rds is that once you get to know the maze a little and memorize the path to RedV, you can just go around killing obsolete models (easy kills) and collecting the fragments which usually takes a while, then going to check for RedV's spawn every once in a while then slay him to death while you still have fragments left for another blackbox.<BR>
<BR>
You can do it either way, it's your choice, but to put it into simple terms - If you want to do this quest and just get one bull smasher while getting some good exp, fight clockworks, If you want a lot of them in a short time, but dont mind small exp, Go find RedV and destroy him and his little turds.<BR>
<BR>
Kivko - The knee-high healer (temp name)</font></td></tr></table>
